    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA378-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu tōḻi ciṟaippuṟamākac colliyatu. 2. talaimakaṉ oruvaḻit taṇantapiṉṉai vaṉpoṟai (ER, EV: vaṉpuṟai) etirmoḻintatūumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what the confidante said when [HE] was behind the fence. 2. It is also how [SHE] was desolate in the face of consolation after HE had departed on a temporary absence.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA378">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>yāmamu neṭiya kaḻiyuṅ kāmamuṅ</l>
<l>kaṇpaṭa līyātu perukun teṇkaṭaṉ</l>
<l>muḻaṅkutirai muḻaviṉ pāṇiyiṟ paipayap</l>
<l>paḻampuṇ ṇuṟunariṟ paravaiyi ṉālu</l>
<l>māṅkavai naliyavu nīṅki yāṅku</l>
<l>miraviṟan tellai tōṉṟala talarvā</l>
<l>yayaliṟ peṇṭir pacalai pāṭa</l>
<l>vīṅkā kiṉṟāṟ ṟōḻi yōṅkumaṇal</l>
<l>variyār ciṟumaṉai citaii vantu</l>
<l>parivutarat toṭṭa paṇimoḻi nampip</l>
<l>pāṭimiḻ paṉinīrc cērppaṉoṭu</l>
<l>nāṭā tiyainta naṇpiṉa taḷavē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>            Won’t we perish, since that [is] a fetter,</l>
<l rend="indent">            experiencing something difficult, being the wish to prepare for</l>
<l rend="indent2">            mounting the palmyra horse, wearing a garland</l>
<l rend="indent2">            [and] praising the beauty of the young woman with bright forehead</l>
<l rend="indent3">            in every village and land of the region of wide area<note place="foot">Can <term xml:lang="ta">kaṇ akal</term> simply be understood as <term xml:lang="ta">akal kaṇ</term>?</note>?</l>
<l>        The small forehead that has joined the hair,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            as the wide moonlight of the fresh-rayed moon</l>
<l rend="indent2">            that had been curtailed by the snake in the wide dark sky,</l>
<l>        has become weakening pain that is murmuring.</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="8+9b">
<l>    It [the fetter] has become a weakening pain that murmurs</l>
<l> 	of the small forehead ...<note place="foot">For reasons of syntax this second version might even be preferable, because it is not usual to have two consecutive <term xml:lang="ta">peyareccam</term> forms in -<term xml:lang="ta">um</term> without a dependant clause.</note></l>
</lg>
        </lg>
      </div>
